Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} on to boil for the noodles. 
Meanwhile, trim the @spring onion{2} and then thinly slice. Peel and grate the 
@ginger{1}(peeled and grated) and @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a 
#garlic press{}). Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lenghways, deseed and finely chop. 
Trim the @green beans{150} then chop into thirds. Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to 
the boiling water and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}.

Meanwhile, pop the ginger, garlic, chilli (use less if you don't like spice!), 
@soy sauce{25}, @honey{15} and @sesame seeds{15} into a #small bowl{} and mix 
together.

Pop a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Add the 
@diced chicken thigh{350} along with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Cook until 
browned, ~{5%minutes}. If your pan is small, cook the chicken in batches as you 
want it to fry rather than stew. Add the green beans and half the spring onion. 
Stir-fry for a further ~{5%minutes}.

When your chicken is cooked through and your beans are tender, pour the sauce 
made in step 2 into the pan. Important: The chicken is cooked when it is no 
longer pink in the middle. Stir together and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, then add 
the cooked noodles. Toss together and cook for another minute until everything 
is nicely combined and piping hot.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all) and roughly 
chop the @salted peanuts{25}(roughly chopped) (or pop them in a #freezer bag{} 
and bash them with a frying pan - depending on your mood!).

Serve your noodles and chicken in #bowls{} with a sprinkling of coriander, 
peanuts and the remaining spring onion. If you have any leftover chopped chilli, 
sprinkle that on too for a bit of kick. Enjoy!

> Honey and soy are two flavours that were made for each other. Sweet, sticky, 
> and with a kick of heat, the delicious sauce in this recipe's guaranteed to 
> take your stir-fry game to new levels of greatness. Quick, easy and bursting 
> with fresh flavours and good-for-you ingredients, this is a great quick fix 
> recipe if you're a little short on time. Don't forget to slurp those noodles!